<div class="allianceSection collapsable collapsed">
	 <h4 class="header">Fire Characteristics</h4>
	<div class="text">Fires in annual herb types result in a short-term increase in available nitrogen and phosphorus (Menke and Rice 1981). Because fine stems generally create low-intensity fires, little heat is transported more than a few centimeters into the soil, and seeds in the soil are generally unaffected.</div>
